The paper deals with transceiver designs in a multiuser MISO downlink channel, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of channel coding, which falls under the category of networked and internet systems (cs.NI). The paper proposes new transceiver strategies for physical-layer multicasting, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
